Jack Wolff is the author and protagonist of the autobiography, Jack leads the reader through his troubled boyhood, which is plagued by domestic abuse and misbehavior. Despite his grim upbringing, Jack remains hopeful and is convinced that he is capable of a better life. In elementary school, Jack change his name from Toby to Jack, after the author ##Jack London# which his mother begrudgingly allows him to do.Read anin-depth analysis of Jack Wolff.